Ritual Houses legitimating rank through ceremony, Predator Bands
mimicking ritual to extract compliance, and Survivor Clusters
bartering in clearings. None controls the whole. The Wardens of Iron
recognize this from Coppersalt Bay's outer island chains -- contested
space where power is local and theatrical. The difference: Kowloon
does not pretend to govern its ungovernable edges. Midgaard does.

The Woodland shows what happens when order as infrastructure is
applied only at boundaries. Roads no longer return to watched squares.
Registry systems lose force where witnesses are scarce. The Courier
Lantern Office translates this: a lantern you cannot maintain is
a promise you should not make.

