incidents as variance, maintain plausible governance at the edge. Our
own Iron Gate faces similar frontier pressure. The difference is
doctrine. We do not classify the ungovernable as variance. We call it
threat, assign it a color, and maintain the gate.

The Eccentric Woodland is Midgaard's problem. It reminds Kowloon:
a city whose lights reach only to the wall is honest. A city
claiming light beyond the wall had better keep those lanterns lit.
